'''Kawata Shrine''' (かわたじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in {{jalink|Kōka City|Q847584}}, {{jalink|Shiga Prefecture|Q131358}}.

=== Enshrined Deities ===
* {{jalink|Ametoyukawa Itage|Q52319907|Ametoyukawa-geta-no-Mikoto}} – ancestral deity of the Tottori no Muraji clan
* Amakawata-na-no-Mikoto
〈Associated Deities〉
* {{jalink|Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto}}

=== Shrine Crest ===
* Descending wisteria

=== History ===
It is traditionally said to have been founded during the reign of {{jalink|Emperor Suinin|Q314850}}. It is a {{jalink|candidate shrine|Q135022904}} of a {{jalink|Myōjin Taisha|Q9610964}} listed in the {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932}}. In {{jalink|Kyōhō|Q1145048}} 11 ({{jalink|1726|Q6936}}), it was granted the divine rank of Senior First Rank ({{jalink|shinkai|Q11591025}}). It served as the {{jalink|sōsha}} of {{jalink|Kurata Estate}}. In {{jalink|Meiji|Q3125096}} 9 ({{jalink|1876|Q7766}}) it was designated a {{jalink|Village Shrine}}, in the same era’s 17th year ({{jalink|1884|Q7819}}) a {{jalink|Township Shrine}}, and in {{jalink|Shōwa|Q327567}} 11 ({{jalink|1936|Q18649}}) it was promoted to a {{jalink|Prefectural Shrine}}.

=== Festivals ===
* Annual Festival  
: Held on April 25.
* Ancient-style Yōya Festival

=== Auxiliary Shrines ===
* Tenmangū

